# BRSR Data Collection — Cursor Rules
# Full codebase context is in CONTEXT.md at the project root. Read it before making changes.

---

## Stack

- Next.js 14 (App Router), TypeScript, Supabase (Auth + Postgres), Tailwind CSS
- Package manager: npm
- Path alias: `@/` → project root

---

## Project areas

- `/master` — Super-admin (role slug: `master`). Manages orgs, users, roles, visibility.
- `/dashboard` — Org users (roles: `admin`, `user`, custom). BRSR questionnaire per org + reporting year.
- Auth: email/password via Supabase. Post-login redirect by role. Middleware handles all role-based routing.

---

## Directory conventions

- `app/(dashboard)/dashboard/hooks/` — Custom React hooks only (`useAnswers`, `useAssignments`, `useAssignmentStats`).
- `app/(dashboard)/dashboard/panels/` — One panel component per BRSR section.
- `lib/brsr/` — All BRSR logic. Never put BRSR business logic in components or API routes.
  - `questionCodes.ts` — All `*_CODES` arrays and `getQuestionCodesForPanel()`. Add new codes here.
  - `calcRules.ts` — `CALC_RULES` array. Add new calc rules here.
  - `calcEngine.ts` — `runCalculations()`. Do not modify unless changing the engine itself.
  - `flowGeneralDataToP6.ts` — General Data → Principle 6 autofill logic.
  - `questionConfig.ts` — Re-export barrel only. Do not add logic here.
- `components/` — Shared, reusable components only (`QuestionInput.tsx` etc.).
- `supabase/migrations/` — SQL migrations. Always add a new numbered file; never edit existing ones.

---

## Supabase client usage

| Context | Import |
|---------|--------|
| Server components, API routes | `createClient()` from `@/lib/supabase/server` |
| Client components | `createClient()` from `@/lib/supabase/client` |
| Admin ops (create user, seed) | `@/lib/supabase/admin` (service role — never expose to client) |

RLS is enforced at the DB layer. Always let RLS do org isolation — do not manually filter by `org_id` in queries unless RLS is not yet in place.

---

## Answers / questionnaire

- One row per `(org_id, reporting_year, question_code)` in the `answers` table. Values are always strings.
- `AnswersState = Record<string, string>` — question_code → value.
- Load via GET `/api/answers?org_id=...&reporting_year=...`. Save via POST `/api/answers` with debounce (`SAVE_DEBOUNCE_MS` from `constants.ts`).
- Calculated fields come from `runCalculations(values)` — they are never stored in the DB; always derive them on the fly.
- General Data → Principle 6 autofill: call `flowGeneralDataToPrinciple6(values)` whenever `gdata_turnover_cy/py` or `gdata_ppp_cy/py` change; merge result into answers state.

