## TypeScript rules

- No `any`. Use `unknown` + type guard if the shape is truly unknown.
- No `React.FC`. Use plain function components with explicit return types.
- Named exports only. No default exports except Next.js page/layout files (required by the framework).
- Zod for all external input validation (API route bodies, form data).
- Return `{ success: boolean; error?: string }` objects from server actions and API handlers — never throw generic `Error`.

---

## API route rules

- All authenticated routes: verify session via `createClient()` from server; rely on RLS for data access.
- Master-only routes: check `role_slug === 'master'` explicitly at the top of the handler before any DB call.
- Admin operations (user create): use `@/lib/supabase/admin`. Never use the service role client in response to user-supplied data without validating role first.
- System roles (`master`, `admin`, `user`) must never be deleted — enforce this in the API, not only the UI.

---

## RLS / database rules

- Never bypass RLS with the service role client in application code. Service role is for seeding and user provisioning only.
- `current_user_org_id()` and `current_user_role_slug()` read from `user_role_slug_cache` — use these in new RLS policies, not `user_role_slug()` (avoids recursion introduced pre-002).
- New migrations: add a new file `supabase/migrations/00N_description.sql`. Never edit existing migration files.

---

## Styling

- Dark theme via `.brsr-dark` class in `globals.css`. Do not add custom colors inline — extend `globals.css` or use the existing Tailwind config.
- Header/sidebar: `#1a202c`. Content area: `#0a0f12`. Borders: `#334155`.
- Use Tailwind utility classes. No CSS modules, no styled-components.

---

## Do not

- Do not add `console.log`. Use the logger utility if one exists; otherwise use `console.error` for errors only.
- Do not duplicate question codes — all codes live in `lib/brsr/questionCodes.ts`.
- Do not put calc logic in components — use `runCalculations()` and pass `calcDisplay` as a prop.
- Do not store calculated values in the `answers` table.
- Do not repeat instructions already present in this file when prompting — reference `CONTEXT.md` or this file instead.
- Do not use agent/auto-apply mode for multi-file refactors without reviewing each file change individually.

